In this article, it is mentioned that the President made separate calls to the Congressional leadership, including Senate Majority Leader Reid, Senate Minority Leader McConnell, Speaker Boehner, and Democratic Leader Pelosi. The President emphasized that Congress needs to pay the bills and pass a budget on time, as failure to do so would harm the economy, small businesses, and middle-class families. The President urged the Republican leadership to pass a bill that funds the government for six weeks without any additional ideological riders. He also stated that he will continue to oppose any attempts to defund or delay the Affordable Care Act and will not negotiate on the debt limit. The President expressed gratitude to the Democratic leaders for their efforts to pass a clean bill that funds the government at current levels and stressed the importance of passing a budget that supports economic growth and benefits the middle class.